Class FunctionModule_WAP

java.lang.Object
  com.mobixell.xtt.FunctionModule
      com.mobixell.xtt.FunctionModule_WAP
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Object>, net.sourceforge.jwap.wsp.IWSPUpperLayer, net.sourceforge.jwap.wsp.IWSPUpperLayer2
public class FunctionModule_WAP
extends FunctionModule
implements net.sourceforge.jwap.wsp.IWSPUpperLayer2

FunctionModule_WAP provides connection-oriented unencrypted wap1 GET functions. It uses the jwap-1.1.jar wap stack from jwap.sourceforge.net.

connectGateway

public void connectGateway(String[] parameters)
connect to a WAP gateway.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters.
parameters[0] argument is always the method name,
parameters[1] argument is the gateway ip address,
parameters[2] is the gateway connection oriented unencrypted port.
If only parameters[0] is submitted the parameters will be taken from the configuration xml document in XTTProperties.
If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.

disconnectGateway

public void disconnectGateway(String[] parameters)
disconnect from a WAP gateway.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters. parameters[0] argument is always the method name. No other arguments required. If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.

checkResponseCode

public void checkResponseCode(String[] parameters)
compare the http response code of the last POST/GET request with a value.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters. parameters[0] argument is always the method name, parameters[1] argument is the post field name, parameters[2] argument and following are concatenated together to the header value.
